Irish texts present their very own ideas about bodies and their role in structuring the narrated worlds of the texts. The study presents one of the first systematic examinations of bodies in these two literary traditions in terms of body criticism and emphasises the ingenuity and complexity of medieval texts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2019) 0aHuman body in literature. 0aIrish literatureyTo 1100xHistory and criticism. 0aOld Norse literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aOther (Philosophy) in literature. 4aAlterität. 4aMedialität. 4aNarratologie. 4aNarratology. 4aalterity. 4abody criticism. 4amediality. 70(DE-601)1054475790(DE-588)4164424-4aKörpergMotiv2gnd 70(DE-601)1057781410(DE-588)4120207-7aIrisch2gnd 70(DE-601)1057786800(DE-588)4120126-7aAltnordisch2gnd 70(DE-601)1062450150(DE-588)4035964-5aLiteratur2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2016z9783110485264oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831104554270 cprintz978311045538040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110455878423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110455878.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGGb2016  aZDB-23-DKUb2016